      "text": "~* TEX>~\n\nP\n\nU\n\nB\n\nL ~\n\nFiling Receipt Filing Date - 2025-03-25 11:59:59 AM Control Number - 57578 Item Number - 13\n\nDOCKET NO. 57578\n\n| APPLICATION OF TEXAS-NEW | | | PUBLIC UTILITY COMMISSION § | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| MEXICO POWER COMPANY FOR | | | § | |\n| INTERIM UPDATE OF WHOLESALE | | | § OF TEXAS | |\n| TRANSMISSION RATES | | | § | |\n\nNOTICE OF APPROVAL This Notice of Approval addresses the application of Texas-New Mexico Power Company (TNMP) for an interim update of its wholesale transmission rates. The Commission adjusts TNMP's annual revenue requirement, on an interim basis, to $175,041,954, and adjusts its wholesale transmission rate, on an interim basis, to $2.159874 per kilowatt (kW), with a corresponding increase in its hourly export rate, effective the date of this Notice of Approval.\n\nI. Findings of Fact \nThe Commission makes the following findings of fact. \nApplicant \n1. TNMP is a Texas corporation registered with the Texas secretary of state under file \nnumber 19241500. \n2. TNMP owns and operates for compensation in Texas facilities and equipment to transmit \nand distribute electricity in the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT) region. \n3. TNMP holds certificate of convenience and necessity number 30038 to provide service to \nthe public. \nApplication \n4. On January 24, 2025, TNMP filed the application at issue in this proceeding seeking an \ninterim update of its previously approved transmission cost of service revenue requirement, \nwholesale transmission rate, and export rate from the ERCOT region. \n5. On March 3,2025, TNMP filed a supplement to WP/Schedule E-2.1.2. \n6. TNMP requested an increase in total transmission rate base of $83,549,611 for a total of \n$175,041,954. \n\n7. TNMP also requested an interim increase in its annual wholesale transmission rate to \n$2.159874 per kW and a corresponding increase in its hourly rate for the transmission of \nelectricity to be exported from the ERCOT region to $0.000247 per kW. \n8. No party filed a motion to find the application materially deficient. \n9. No order was issued finding the application materially deficient. \n10. In Order No. 2 filed on February 18, 2025, the administrative law judge (ALJ) found the \napplication administratively complete. \nNotice \n11. On January 28, 2025, TNMP filed the affidavit of Cathie Piontek, paralegal at TNMP, \nattesting that, on January 27,2025, notice of the application was mailed or emailed to all \nparties in TNMP' s last transmission cost of service proceeding, Docket No. 48401,1 and to \nevery distribution service providers listed in the matrix utilized by the Commission in \nDocket No. 56050,2 which established the wholesale transmission charges for the calendar \nyear 2024. \n12. In Order No. 2 filed on February 18, 2025, the ALJ found notice of the application \nsufficient. \nIntervention \n13. No person filed a motion to intervene. \nEvidentiarr Record \n14. In Order No. 3 filed on March 25, 2025, the ALJ admitted the following evidence into the \nrecord ofthis proceeding: \na. TNMP's application and all attachments filed on January 24,2025; \nb. TNMP's proof of notice filed on January 28,2025; \n\n1 Application of Texas - New Mexico Power Company to Change Rates , Docket No . 48401 , Order (Dec. 20,2018) 2 Commission Staff's Petition to Set 2024 Wholesale Transmission Service Charges for the Electric Reliability Council of Texas , Inc , Docket No . 56050 , Order May 16 , 2024 )\n\nc. Commission Staff' s recommendation on material deficiency filed on February 14, \n2025; \nd. TNMP's supplement to the application filed on March 3,2025; and \ne. Commission Staff's recommendation on final disposition filed on March 10, 2025. \nElij:ibilitv for Interim Update \n15. TNMP's last interim update to its transmission rates was approved on September 20,2024, \nin Docket No. 56860. \n16. This application is TNMP's first requested interim increase initiated in 2025. \nInterim Transmission Rate \n17. TNMP's application compares the actual December 31, 2024, transmission net plant \nbalances against the incremental amounts approved in Docket No. 56860. The difference \nbetween these two balances provides the basis for the increase in the rate base for TNMP \nin this application. \n18. The requested interim increase in transmission rates reflect a total rate base in this filing of \n$1,177,438,393, with an interim revenue requirement increase of $83,549,611, for a total \ninterim transmission cost of service revenue requirement of $175,041,954. \n19. The requested interim wholesale transmission rate is based on the average 2025 ERCOT \nfour-coincident-peak demand of 81,042,656.6 kW identified in the draft transmission \ncharge matrix filed by Commission Staff in Docket No. 57491.3 \n20. The requested interim increase in the wholesale transmission rate accurately reflects \nadditions and retirements of TNMP' s transmission facilities as well as changes to return \non rate base, depreciation and amortization, taxes other than income taxes, and federal \nincome taxes associated with the additional rate base. \nInterim Revenue Requirement \n21. TNMP's request reflects an interim increase of $11,500,427 in TNMP's transmission rate \nbase to a total interim transmission rate base of $175,041,954. \n\n3 Commission Staff's Petition to Set 2025 Wholesale Transmission Service Charges for the Electric Reliability Council of Texas , Inc ., Docket No . 57491 , Commission Staff ' s Draft Transmission Charge Matrix (Feb. 27,2025)\n\n22. TNMP's request uses a rate of return for TCOS investment of 7.89% approved in Docket \nNo. 48401. \n23. The interim revenue requirement reflects operations and maintenance of $7,064,252; \ndepreciation and amortization of $52,753,941; taxes other than income taxes of \n$13,217,526, federal income taxes of $9,092,751; a return on rate base of $92,899,889; \nother expense of $280,227; and other revenues of negative $266,633. \nERCOT Export Rate \n24. TNMP requested Commission approval of an ERCOT hourly export rate of $0.000247 per \nkW. \nInformal Disposition \n25. More than 15 days have passed since the completion of the notice provided in this docket. \n26. No person filed a protest or motion to intervene. \n27. TNMP and Commission Staff are the only parties to this proceeding. \n28. No party requested a hearing, and no hearing is needed. \n29. Commission Staff recommended approval of the application, subject to a more \ncomprehensive analysis and reconciliation at the next complete review of TNMP' s \ntransmission cost of service. \n30. This decision is not adverse to any party. \nII. Conclusions of Law \nThe Commission makes the following conclusions of law. \n1. The Commission has authority over this application under PURA4§§ 32.001 and 35.004. \n2. TNMP is a public utility as defined in PURA § 11.004 and an electric utility as defined in \nPURA § 31.002(6). \n3. TNMP is a transmission service provider as defined in 16 Texas Administrative Code \n(TAC) § 25.5(141), that provides transmission service as defined in PURA § 31.002(20). \n\n4 Public Utility Regulatory Act, Tex. Util. Code §§ 11.001-66.016.\n\n4. TNMP provided notice ofthe application in accordance with 16 TAC § 25.192(h)(4)(A) \n5. As a transmission service provider in the ERCOT region, TNMP may update its \ntransmission rates, on an interim basis, to reflect changes in its invested capital \nunder 16 TAC § 25.192(h)(1). \n6. The interim rates set in this Notice of Approval must be reconciled as provided in 16 TAC \n§25.192(h)(2) \n7. TNMP's application complies with the requirements of 16 TAC § 25.192(h)(1). \n8. TNMP's application was deemed sufficient in accordance with 16 TAC § 25.192(h)(4)(B). \n9. This application does not constitute a major rate case proceeding as defined in 16 TAC \n§ 22.2(27). \n10. The interim rates established in this Notice of Approval are just and reasonable under \nPURA § 36.003(a). \n11. The interim rates established in this Notice of Approval are not unreasonably preferential, \nprejudicial, or discriminatory,",
